# AdEMLync Project Rules

## Communication Language
- Communicate with user in Russian language
- All code comments, variable names, menu items, and messages must be in English
- Reports go to `reports/` folder with sequential numbering (01, 02, 03, etc.)

## Output Formatting
- Do NOT use ANSI escape codes
- Do NOT use Unicode symbols for decoration
- Do NOT use colored ANSI codes
- Keep output minimal and to the point
- No flame or unnecessary verbosity

## Table Formatting
- Use monospace code blocks for tables instead of Markdown tables
- Do NOT use Markdown table syntax (| col1 | col2 |)
- Use fenced code blocks (```) with fixed-width text alignment
- Align columns with spaces for readability

## Git and Version Control
- Do NOT commit anything without explicit user request
- Do NOT modify git config
- Always verify changes before commit

## Reports and Documentation
- Keep all existing reports
- Do NOT create new reports without user request
- When creating reports, place them in `reports/` folder
- Use sequential numbering: 01_, 02_, 03_, etc.
- Reports content should be in Russian

## Code Standards
- Follow Dart/Flutter best practices
- Use English for all identifiers and comments
- Maintain existing code style
- Test changes before suggesting them

## Project Structure
- Main app: `ademlync/` - Flutter mobile application
- Device package: `packages/ademlync_device/` - BLE communication with AdEM devices
- Cloud package: `packages/ademlync_cloud/` - AWS cloud integration

## Technology Stack
- Flutter/Dart for mobile development
- BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy) for device communication
- AWS API Gateway for cloud services
- AdEM Key and Air Console dongles for BLE bridge

## File Types in Project
- Dart files (*.dart) - main codebase
- C files (*.c, *.h) - potential test cases
- Python files (*.py) - scripts and tests
- PowerShell files (*.ps1) - Windows automation
- Batch files (*.bat, *.cmd) - Windows scripts
